Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil over high heat. When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{3} to the pot, remove from the heat and leave for ~{3%minutes}. After 3 mins, drain your noodles into a #colander{} and then run under cold water to stop them cooking any further.

Remove the core from the @green pepper{2} and thinly slice. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice into half moon shapes.

Cut the top and bottom off the @carrot{1}, peel and then use your #peeler{} to make carrot ribbons. Run the peeler from the very top of your carrot to the bottom. Repeat until all of your carrot is used up. Pop your carrot ribbons into a #bowl{} and keep to one side for later. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Peel and grate the @ginger{1} and then thinly slice the @red chilli{1}.

> The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== Pork ==

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add a splash of @oil{a splash} and when it's hot add the @pork medallion{4}. Cook for ~{6%minutes} on each side, turning halfway through. You want the pork to be golden brown on both sides.

== Vegetables ==

Whilst your pork cooks, heat another frying pan or a #wok{} over high heat and add a splash of @oil{a splash}. Add your pepper and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Move your pepper around every minute or so to ensure even cooking. After 5 mins add your onion and cook for another ~{2%minutes}. Next add your garlic and ginger and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

== Sauce and Assembly ==

Pour in the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}, a third of the @hoisin sauce{3%tbsp} and the @water{50%ml}. Heat until your sauce bubbles, then stir in your noodles. Reduce the heat to low and cook for another ~{3%minutes} until your noodles are piping hot. Stir through the @beansprouts{1} and cook for a further ~{30%seconds}.

When your pork is cooked, remove the pan from the heat, drain off any excess oil and stir in the rest of your hoisin sauce. Roll your pork around in your hoisin sauce. Squeeze the juice from the @lime{1} and stir into your carrot ribbons.

Serve a generous amount of your noodles on a #plate{} and top with some carrot ribbons. Cut each pork medallion into six slices and pop on top of your noodles and carrot. Spoon over your hoisin sauce from the pan. Finish with a few slices of chilli.